  "text": "Review from computational geometry: There are classical results in computational geometry regarding uniformly sampling from the plane. The results related the area of the convex-hull to the total area of the convex domain from which the points are sampled at uniform. For a set of points Z let ConvexHull(Z) be their convex hull and for a body Y let area(Y ) be its area. The following theorem summarizes the related results (see, cf., [CITATION_1] ).",
